Use load() from YamlConfiguration object.
public static YamlConfiguration loadConfiguration(@NotNull Reader reader) {
    Validate.notNull(reader, "Stream cannot be null");

    YamlConfiguration config = new YamlConfiguration();

    try {
        config.load(reader);
    } catch (IOException ex) {
        Bukkit.getLogger().log(Level.SEVERE, "Cannot load configuration from stream", ex);
    } catch (InvalidConfigurationException ex) {
        Bukkit.getLogger().log(Level.SEVERE, "Cannot load configuration from stream", ex);
    }

    return config;
}
When IOException or InvalidConfigurationException occurs it will result in NPE since Bukkit.getServer() returns null until CraftServer sets Bukkit.setServer(...) in its constructor.
